article.headline: Texas-Arlington 69, Stephen F. Austin 62
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Vereen scored 19 points and Texas-Arlington went on to beat Stephen F. Austin 69-62 on Saturday. Texas-Arlington (12-16, 7-8 Southland) led 35-34 at the half. Also scoring in double digits for Texas-Arlington were Ro'ger Guignard with 11 and Tommy Moffitt and Larry Posey with 10 each. Vereen was 5-of-9 from the field. Vereen had 13 rebounds and Moffitt had 10. For Stephen F. Austin (15-11, 8-6), Antuane Miller led with 15 points. He was followed by Trevor Guy with 14. Miller was 6-of-13 from the field. Guy and Miller each had six rebounds.
